remove files using terminal
ex. 	data/test
		test/a.js ,test/a.php ,test/a.css ,
	now you want to del test folder
	
cd data
rm -rf test

------------------------------------------------------------------------
Find location of php.ini

php --ini

if php is install this command will run

else you have to run first this one

sudo apt-get install php5-cli

then run 

php --ini

it will give result as 

Configuration File (php.ini) Path: /etc/php5/cli
Loaded Configuration File:         /etc/php5/cli/php.ini
Scan for additional .ini files in: /etc/php5/cli/conf.d
Additional .ini files parsed:      /etc/php5/cli/conf.d/pdo.ini



